<Folder><name>Start / End</name><Placemark><name>START: Chiang Mai</name><styleUrl>#start</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>98.985300,18.788300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>END: Chiang Rai</name><styleUrl>#end</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.840600,19.910500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Chiang Dao</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>98.966700,19.366700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Doi Ang Khang turnoff</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.001900,19.544400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Fang</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.215000,19.915600,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tha Ton</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.363300,20.066400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Doi Mae Salong</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.519700,20.092800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Doi Tung area</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.636100,20.163900,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mae Sai (Myanmar border)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>99.881900,20.429700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Sop Ruak (Golden Triangle)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>100.082500,20.358300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Chiang Saen</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>100.083300,20.275000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Chiang Dao</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[The 2,225 m Doi Chiang Dao limestone massif drops sharply from rice fields. Chiang Dao Cave runs 5+ km into the mountain — the first 360 m is well-developed with Buddha images; deeper sections need a guide with a lantern.]]></description><Point><coordinates>98.966700,19.366700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Tha Ton</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[River town on the Kok. Long-tail boats run downstream to Chiang Rai (4 hrs) — a quietly beautiful slow trip past hill-tribe villages. Wat Tha Ton's hilltop terraces have nine temples on ascending levels.]]></description><Point><coordinates>99.363300,20.066400,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Doi Mae Salong</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[1,800 m village built by Kuomintang 93rd Division refugees in 1961. Yunnanese architecture, Chinese cemeteries, tea terraces. Best visited late January for cherry blossoms (sakura). The Chinese Martyrs Memorial Hall tells the strange political story.]]></description><Point><coordinates>99.519700,20.092800,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Mae Sai</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Thailand's northernmost town and a road border with Myanmar's Tachileik. The 2018 Tham Luang cave rescue happened in the hills 60 km southwest.]]></description><Point><coordinates>99.881900,20.429700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Golden Triangle</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Confluence of the Ruak and Mekong rivers — Thailand on the south bank, Myanmar to the west, Laos to the east. The Hall of Opium museum tells the unsanitized history of the trade that financed half the region for 200 years.]]></description><Point><coordinates>100.082500,20.358300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Chiang Rai / Wat Rong Khun</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[The 'White Temple' (1997, ongoing) is artist Chalermchai Kositpipat's surreal vision of Buddhist iconography — bone-white plaster, mirror inlays, demon-clawed bridges. Free entry.]]></description><Point><coordinates>99.840600,19.910500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
</Document></kml>
